76561197994679756,Recommended,305800,16318382,"Posted: 11 June, 2015",all,Desk Rabbit,"RECOMMENDED HIGHLYTRIPPY: RETRO: EXPERIMENTAL: SOUNDTRACKMany don't know this, but POP is a game from another dimension. Really. I'm not kidding.Often on sale for under $2 or even $0.99, buying POP is a no brainer for fans of video games who appreciate creativity, experimentation, interactive experiences, and wild aesthetics, as well as great music and sound design. Actually, the music is better than great.Fans of trippy games or interactive experiences should absolutely get this without a second thought. Yes, it is short. I guess a first playthrough took me about 20 minutes, but it is a memorable experience and has great replayability. It's an immersive 20 minutes to say the least. You will be entertained, perplexed at times, and surprised. I've never played anything else like it .To put it simply, the game has 7 minigames sandwiched between interesting imagery and short video montages. It is up to the player to figure out how to play the minigames. And for a few, the objective isn't even readily apparent.You'll be dropped into a boat during a thunderstorm, a highway car race, a war helicopter, a walk in the desert, a space shuttle launch, and a game similar to Missile Command. The presentation of the games is very pixelish and retro. Even outside of the minigames, pressing certain keys will affect music and artwork. The main menu itself is an exercise in interactive experimentation. The music is FANTASTIC.I got the game on sale for over a dollar I think. It is always on sale. But, for real fans of this sort of thing, the full price of $3.99 is very reasonable. It's the price of a fancy cup of coffee or a beer. This will stay with you long after playing just once. I've played this at least 5 times and still notice new things. Did I mention the OST?"
